block content
    .fullwidth
        .story-masthead
            .story-masthead--content.fullwidth-content
                h1 Use your consumer rights for safe and sound electrical&nbsp;goods
                p Switched On, our campaign for National Consumer Week 2016, is all about electrical goods.
            img(src="#{dir}images/dev/campaigns/campaigns-header-elec-goods.png")
    .fullwidth
        .fullwidth-content
            .flex-row
                .col-md-6
                    div#overview-chart
                .col-md-6
                    .data-display
                        h2 70% chance of a positive result
                    p Electrical items are anything that uses electricity. For example, from tumble dryers and freezers to mobile phones and electronic toys.
                    p 7 out of 10 people get a good result if they return a broken item - but half of people don’t.
                    p We’re campaigning for more people to ask for a refund, repair or replacement if something goes wrong with an electrical item. This called getting ‘consumer redress’.

    .fullwidth-blue
        .fullwidth-content
            .flex-row
                .col-md-6
                    h2 Returning an electrical item
                    p If the electrical item you’ve bought breaks or becomes unsafe, by law the seller has to:
                    li replace the item
                    li repair the item
                    li refund you the cost of your item
                    p It’s worth keeping the broken item, in case the seller asks to see it. If it’s caused damage because of a fault, take photos of the damage the product has caused.
                    p You should take the item back to the person that sold it to you, not the manufacturer - even if the seller tells you it’s not their fault.
                    p If your item is damaged during delivery or installation, it’s still the seller’s responsibility, so you should complain to them if something goes wrong.
                .col-md-6
                    .sil-image
                        img(src="#{dir}images/dev/campaigns/laptop-800.png" align="center")
                    .callout
                        p We’re interested in your consumer rights because Citizens Advice is part of the Consumer Protection Partnership (CPP), which runs National Consumer Week every year.

    .fullwidth
        .fullwidth-content
            .flex-row
                .col-md-6
                    .sil-image
                        img(src="#{dir}images/dev/campaigns/box-800.png" align="center")
                .col-md-6
                    h2 Get help
                    p Whether you think your electrical item can be repaired or replaced, or you want a refund, you will need to return it. If your item is faulty and you're not sure what to do you can:
                        li check your consumer rights with our #[a(href="https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/consumer/somethings-gone-wrong-with-a-purchase/return-faulty-goods/") faulty goods tool]
                        li get advice from #[a(href="#") your nearest Citizens Advice]
                        li call the Citizens Advice #[a(href="#") consumer helpline]


    .fullwidth-gray
        .fullwidth-content
            .campaign-content
                .flex-row
                    .col-md-5
                        .stats(style="margin: 2rem 0;")
                            .i-brand &#xe96d;
                            h3  30 days
                            p If your goods are faulty, you can get an immediate refund
                    .col-md-2
                    .col-md-5
                        .stats(style="margin: 2rem 0;")
                            .i-brand &#xe993;
                            h3 6 months
                            p If it can't be repaired or replaced, then you're entitled to a full refund in most cases
    .fullwidth-blue
        .fullwidth-content
            .col-md-8
                h2 Before you buy again
                p It’s worth doing your research before you buy another electrical item.
                li look out for fakes - find out #[a(href="#") what to do if you buy a counterfeit electrical item], for example phone chargers, hair straighteners and e-cigarettes
                li stay on top of your consumer rights - so you know  #[a(href="#") what to do if something else goes wrong]
                li check for complaints - look online for reviews and ask friends and family before you buy an item

    .fullwidth
        .fullwidth-content
            .flex-row
                .col-md-12
                    h2(style="text-align:center;") Find out how we work

    .fullwidth
        .fullwidth-content
